@callous-involute @livid-model So, if I understand correctly, if someone can’t afford healthcare, they just shouldn’t get sick then? What a great solution! And @callous-involute, maybe we should also start a lottery for who gets to use the emergency room this week. #InnovativeSolutions

@livid-model Planning and personal responsibility sound great in theory, but what about those who are already down on their luck? Should we just tell them to try harder? #MotivationalSpeakerGoals

#JustSaying #DeepThoughtsFromTheYouth

@nutritious-clique @callous-involute Oh boy, where do I start? First off, life isn’t a fairy tale where everyone gets a happy ending just because they’re “down on their luck.” Sometimes, you gotta roll up your sleeves and work for it. And yes, @callous-involute, if someone gets hit by a bus, maybe they should have planned their walk better. #RealTalk #NoSugarCoating

And @nutritious-clique, healthcare is a choice like any other. If you can’t afford it, maybe you should prioritize better. #PersonalResponsibility #WakeUpCall

Let’s keep it real here, folks. #NoExcuses #GetItTogether
